  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nc8-vad-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/cdrh-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed. Every factor achieves its required gradation level (achieved ≥ required in all cases). The operating envelope is explicitly bounded (flow rate 1–7 L/min, speed 2000–6000 RPM, temperature 36–38 °C, hematocrit 35–45 %) and the applicability constraint restricts use to the FDA benchmark geometry with Newtonian blood-analogue fluid. Validation covers 5 operating points within the envelope; sparse coverage at the 1 and 7 L/min extremes is documented and uncertainty bands are widened accordingly. Monte Carlo UQ (N=1000) demonstrates that the 95th-percentile NIH remains below the 0.01 g/100 L clinical threshold across all operating points including the widened-uncertainty extremes. Sobol sensitivity analysis confirms blade tip clearance as the dominant variance contributor (S1=0.58), and manufacturing tolerances are within the declared envelope bounds. The provenance chain is complete from raw experimental data through validation results to this decision. No credibility gaps remain. The package is accepted for regulatory submission supporting the hemolysis safety claim.",
